42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.282f46d8-5423-4b9a-9950-d579235fd9b7.prompt=Artifact ID 42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.2c2c6d12-aef4-47e4-9354-d1faa70c78ba.description=
Checks if a number or word is greater than another number or word. Word comparison is case-sensitive in alphabetical order.

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
value1 > value2

Responses\:
success - The boolean operation was evaluated to true.
failure - Something went wrong or the boolean operation returned false.
42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.3ff86a2d-1849-4acb-acf5-d2d0091e3a3e.prompt=Component ID 42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.41d4f687-4e8e-4efa-a856-b6916634d7b2.prompt=Component ID 42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.431bad9e-af71-40a7-ac03-0e39bc33f47e.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.4766b66d-53c9-40af-b57f-d5375bcc6875.prompt=User Identifier 42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.47bbf993-4667-4dd0-aa06-31433f1159a2.description=
This flow runs an existing script, specified by name, against a device. If no variant of the script supports a given device, that device will be skipped. The script is run as a system
task. The device should be discovered by netwrok automation portal in advance.We assume that the command script has been tested manually and executes successfully from the NA portal.

Inputs\:
naHost		\: The DNS name or IP Address of your NAS core.
naPort		\: The port to connect to your NAS core on.
naProtocol		\: The protocol to connect to your NAS core with. Either HTTP or HTTPS.
naUsername		\: The username for the NAS core.
naPassword		\: The password for the NAS user.
scriptName		\: The Script / command name which is already imported and present in NA portal
isAdvanced		\: Should the command be an advanced script? By default  value is false
switchIPAddres	\: The IP address of the network device.
scriptVariables        	\: A list of variables to be replaced in the script. These are provided as a list of name\=value pairs, separated 
                    		  by commas. Values can be surrounded in single-quotes ('). Within a quoted value, a single-quote can be embedded 
                   		  with two single-quote characters. Example\: "variable1\=value1,varable2\='this is ''value 2'''"
Responses\:
success         	\: The operation completed successfully.
failure        		\: Something went wrong.

Returns\:
returnResult   	\: Text result of NAS script run

Extra Results\:
commandStatus	\: The status of the NAS command.
text            		\: The response text of the NAS command.
stackTrace      	\: The stack trace (If any) of the NAS command.

seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ 42e3e768-362d-45dc-a200-25232789d2de.description=
This workflow performs Virtual Network Deploy operation on the virtual network identified by CSA Service Component.

Inputs\:

CSA_CONTEXT_ID 	\: CSA Context Id
CSA_PROCESS_ID 	\: CSA Process Instance Id
SVC_COMPONENT_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Service component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:SVC_COMPONENT_ID]
RSC_PROVIDER_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource Provider Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\:RSC_PROVIDER_ID]
SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL \: This token will resolve to the subscriber’s email address. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_EMAIL]
RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource Subscription Id that was created from the Resource Offering at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE 	\: This token will resolve to the Service component type. Eg\: Server.. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_COMPONENT_TYPE]
RSC_POOL_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource pool Id that was selected at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_POOL_ID]
SVC_INSTANCE_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Service Instance Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_INSTANCE_ID]
SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Subscription Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: SVC_SUBSCRIPTION_ID]
PRN_COMPONENT_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the parent Component’s Service Component Id. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: PRN_COMPONENT_ID]
REQ_ORG_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_ORG_ID]
REQ_USER_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the User Id associated with the service request. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: REQ_USER_ID]
USR_ORG_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Organization Id associated with the subscriber. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: USR_ORG_ID]
RSC_BINDING_ID 	\: This token will resolve to the Resource Binding Id that was created at the Subscription time. Default value for this token is [TOKEN\: RSC_BINDING_ID]

These tokens with the default values are resolved by CSA when the flow is invoked.

Responses\:
success 		\: Workflow completed successfully.
failure 		\: Something went wrong.
